Q">When you move beyond trillions, there are some extremely mind-bending nu=
mbers, says Richard Fisher. Some of them are too large to fit in the mind =
=E2=80=93 or even within the known Universe.</b></p><p class=3D"sc-9a00e533=
-0 eZyhnA">What's the biggest number you can think of? When I was a child, =
it's the kind of question we'd ask each other in the school playground. Som=
eone would say something hopelessly na=C3=AFve like "a billion billion bill=
ion", only to be outstripped by a peer who knew about trillions, squillions=
 or kajillions (it didn't matter if only one of those is real).</p><p class=
=3D"sc-9a00e533-0 eZyhnA">Eventually, someone would remember that they knew=
 the winning answer: "infinity!" But the smugness was short-lived. Another =
kid =E2=80=93 with a mathematical mic drop =E2=80=93 soon pointed out that =
they could beat it, with "infinity=E2=80=A6 plus one".</p><p class=3D"sc-9a=
00e533-0 eZyhnA">Trying to imagine and understand very big numbers, however=
, is more than just playground game. It's a task that mathematicians have t=
hought about for centuries. They've proposed the existence of numbers that =
are so enormous that no human being has ever successfully brought them to m=
ind in full, let alone written them down. And as for infinity, it turns out=
 there is more than one of those =E2=80=93 and, counterintuitively, some in=
finities are bigger than others.</p><section class=3D"sc-2d378821-0 euNrot"=
><div class=3D"sc-2d378821-1 feVspF"><p class=3D"sc-2d378821-3 fnUMpb">Imme=
nsities</p><div class=3D"sc-2d378821-2 hShVZE"><div class=3D"sc-2d378821-4 =
lcQeVQ"><p class=3D"sc-9a00e533-0 eZyhnA">This article is part of a BBC Fut=
ure series called <a target=3D"_self" href=3D"https://www.bbc.com/future/co=
lumns/immensities" class=3D"sc-f9178328-0 iCaRzc">Immensities</a>. Through =
stories from the worlds of science, philosophy, psychology and history, our=
 goal is to see the world with fresh eyes: nature at its grandest, and the =
human world at its most awe-inspiring.</p></div></div></div></section></div=
